The paper discusses the citation patterns of Sleeping Beauties in science, particularly those cited in patents. This involves analyzing the evolution of scientific literature related to the Sleeping Beauty, as well as the citing and cited relations of the Sleeping Beauty. This suggests a focus on digital libraries (cs.DL) and information retrieval (cs.IR) for analyzing the literature, as well as social and information networks (cs.SI) for analyzing the citing and cited relations. Additionally, the paper discusses the potential for new inventions and innovations, which could fall under computational creativity (cs.CY) and machine learning (cs.LG).
